track_notes: On Nov. 12, 2022, W2SWA and myself (K2JB) attempted to ascend and activate Skunk Ridge (W4T/SU-111). We hiked into Backcountry Campsite #14 the previous day via Hannah Mtn Trail and began our bushwhack to Skunk Ridge at 7:15 AM.  Going was very difficult with steep slopes, significant blowdowns and thick rhododendron.  After 3.5 miles and 4.5 hrs of travel, we encountered unending blowdowns blocking our way.  Additionally, we determined that there was not enough time to activate and return to camp before dark.  Therefore we abandoned our activation attempt. On the return path, we ascended and traversed the 2,000 ft elevation profile of the ridges which helped avoid the thick vegetation on the lower slopes and creek bottoms. This area of the Great Smoky Mtn NP is the most remote area in the park.  After attempting this activation and abandoning it, it is our opinion that this summit is unreachable and should not be attempted by even the most skilled off-trail hiker.
